KEY DESIGN DECISIONS + WHY:
- Exported api.ts `request` instead of duplicating fetch logic. The wrapper
  spreads `...init` AFTER the default headers object, so passing `headers` in
  init REPLACES the default `Content-Type: application/json` wholesale. importCsv
  exploits this: it passes only `{ Accept }`, letting the browser set the
  multipart boundary. A JSON content-type on a FormData body silently corrupts
  the upload — sync.test.ts asserts the content-type is absent to lock this in.
- JournalIsland owns syncStatus and polls (per spec Step 12); ConnectionPanel is
  a controlled child. Two callbacks: onStatusChange (connect/disconnect return
  fresh status, counts unchanged) and onDataChanged (import/reconcile changed
  data → parent refetches trades+stats + re-reads status).
- Live-refetch watermark: a ref initialized null on first poll (so mount does NOT
  double-refetch the data the mount effect already loaded). Refetch fires only
  when trades_dxtrade OR last_fill_at grows. connect/disconnect + post-import both
  call rememberStatus to advance the watermark so the next poll doesn't see
  spurious "growth" and refetch redundantly.
- statusMeta + formatDedupe are exported PURE functions so connectionPanel.test
  asserts "badge label per status" and "dedupe summary formatting" render-free
  (the spec's two stated test targets). The dedupe wording uses the more detailed
  spec phrasing: "N imported · M skipped as duplicates · K flagged for review".
- SourceBadge shows Manual(neutral)/Auto(blue) + amber review chip; when
  duplicate_of is set the chip's tooltip points at the overlapping manual trade —
  reinforcing the spec rule that a flagged import is never silently deleted.
  data-testid="source-badge" + data-source make the E2E badge assertion robust.

E2E NOTE (operational):
- The dev server registers the guarded /api/sync/_test/ingest route because
  DevelopmentConfig.DEBUG=True (views/__init__ gate). The E2E's exact-P&L
  assertion ($995.50 = 40 ticks × $12.50 × 2 − $4.50, the same ES round-trip as
  the manual E2E) requires the ES tick spec seeded; on a fresh DB the instruments
  table is empty and reconciliation would emit tick_size=0 / needs_review / $0.
  Fix: run script/db-seed (idempotent instrument upsert) before E2E. Documented
  in AGENTS.md.

